{{refimprove|date=May 2018}}
The '''Illinois College of Photography and Bissell College of Photo Engraving''' was a college in [[Effingham, Illinois]] opened in 1893 and closed in 1931,<ref name="dailynews">{{cite web |last1=Donaldson |first1=Delaine |title=Effingham's Illinois College of Photography |url=http://www.effinghamdailynews.com/news/lifestyles/effingham-s-illinois-college-of-photography/article_d4f0b739-2e3d-5322-a188-9846284466fe.html |website=Effingham Daily News |accessdate=1 July 2018 |language=en}}</ref> with a focus on practical, vocational photographic training.<ref name="catalog">{{cite book |title=Illinois College of Photography :Effingham, Illinois 1905-1906. |date=1905-1906 |page=7 |url=https://hdl.handle.net/2027/uiuo.ark:/13960/t25b01d3k |accessdate=1 July 2018}}</ref>
The college was founded by photographer Lewis H. Bissell,<ref name="dailynews2">{{cite web |last1=Lewis |first1=Phil |title=Vintage views from the Illinois College of Photography |url=http://www.effinghamdailynews.com/news/local_news/vintage-views-from-the-illinois-college-of-photography/article_0c7fd9e0-31c1-586c-a042-c016575fdae5.html |website=Effingham Daily News |accessdate=1 July 2018 |language=en}}</ref> and was located initially on the Austin College campus in [[Effingham County, Illinois|Effingham County]], Illinois. It later moved to its separate studio and buildings in 1900 at 910–945 Wabash Ave in Effingham. At one time the school had several hundred students from the U.S., Canada and 52 countries.
The college closed in 1931, due to poor enrollment during the [[Great Depression]].<ref name="dailynews" />
Graduates were expected to "go out fully equipped and the fact that they are alumni of the Illinois College of Photography is a guarantee that they are artists in their lines. A diploma from this institution assures them the most remunerative positions in the best studios in the country."
==Notable graduates== * [[Fred Hultstrand]] (1888–1968), graduate 1911 * [[Edward Weston]] (1886–1958), attended 1908–1911 * [[Ellery Valdimir Wilcox]] (1882–1960) * [[T. J. Hileman|Tomar J. Hileman]] (1882–1945), Glacier National Park photographer * [[Avery E. Field]] (1883-1955), graduated 1906<ref name="rpl">{{cite web |title=Riverside Public Library : Local History : Finding aids |url=https://riversideca.gov/library/history_aids_averyfield.asp |website=riversideca.gov |accessdate=1 July 2018}}</ref>
==External links== *{{ Citation | last=Banbury | first=Larry Francis | title=The Sesquicentennial of Effingham Co., 1831-1981 | publisher=Banbury Publishing Company | place=Illinois | year=1982 | url = }}. *{{ Citation | last= | first= | title=The Illinois College of Photography Bulletin, 1905 | publisher= | place=Illinois | year=1905 | url = https://archive.org/details/illinoiscollegeo00illi }}.
