{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Vidyagauri Adkar | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = 250px | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = Marathi | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]] | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | nationality = [[India]] | ethnicity = | citizenship = Indian | education = [[Indian classical dance]], [[Hindustani classical music]] | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Dancer|Classical Dancer]] | years_active = | organization = | style = [[Kathak]] | awards = }}
'''Vidyagauri Adkar''' ([[Marathi language|Marathi]]:विद्यागौरी आडकर) is [[Kathak]] dance exponents in [[India]] and representing the [[Jaipur gharana]] [[Indian classical dance]]. She has performed in many music festivals including Khajuraho Festival of Dances, Chilanka Dance Festival in Thiruvananthapuram, Festival of Dance and Music, Delhi etc.<ref>[http://www.photonicyatra.com/keyword/Vidyagauri%20Adkar/ Vidyagauri Adkar]</ref><ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/dance/classic-moves/article6744463.ece Chilanka Dance Festival in Thiruvananthapuram featured promising dancers performing different classical dances of India]</ref>
==Career== Adkar started her dance career initially in [[Borivali]], [[Mumbai]] and in [[Pune]] during her school and college education. She is Pune University ranker in MSc - [[Mathematics]]. She was awarded by the famous scientist [[Jayant Narlikar]]. She moved to Delhi for higher studies and she is performing extensively for one decade.<ref>[https://www.trackampus.com/home/eventdetail/746 Vidyagauri Adkar]</ref><ref>[http://9dil.us/d-x23fep4.html?Kathak%20musician%20Vidyagauri%20Adkar%20and%20his%20group Adkar]</ref> She has worked on Kathak dancing and has given many brilliant performance. She has performed in many parts of [[India]] and also in [[South Africa]].<ref>[http://udaipurnews.in/2013/03/25/in-other-frozen-city-palace-dhoom-mcyo-hori-ri/ खूब जमी सिटी पैलेस में ‘होरी धूम मच्यो री]</ref>
==Music Festivals== * Khajuraho Festival of Dances, [[Khajuraho]] <ref>[http://www.buzzintown.com/bhopal/events/khajuraho-dance-festival-day-4/id--877836.html Khajuraho festival]</ref> * Chilanka Dance Festival in [[Thiruvananthapuram]] * Festival of Dance and Music, [[Delhi]] * "Anvarat" Kathak performance * Kathak Prabha – Festival of India in South Africa <ref>[http://www.indianspice.co.za/2014/08/kathak-prabha-festival-of-india-in-sa/ Kathak Prabha – Festival of India in SA]</ref> * 2012 Kathak Mahotsava,Delhi<ref>[http://www.sangeetnatak.gov.in/uploads/2012-13/AR_SNA-11-12-PhotographEnglish.pdf Kathak Mahotsava 2012]</ref>
